Source: jolicloud-meta
Section: jolicloud/metapackages
Priority: standard
Maintainer: Jolicloud developers <developers@jolicloud.org>
Standards-Version: 3.8.0
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 4)

Package: jolicloud-minimal
Architecture: any
Depends: ${jolicloud-minimal:Depends}
Recommends: ${jolicloud-minimal:Recommends}
Breaks: ${jolicloud-minimal:Breaks}
Conflicts: ubuntu-minimal
Provides: ubuntu-minimal
Replaces: ubuntu-minimal
Description: Minimal core of Jolicloud
 This package depends on all of the packages in the Jolicloud minimal system,
 that is a functional command-line system with the following capabilities:
 .
  - Boot
  - Detect hardware
  - Connect to a network
  - Install packages
  - Perform basic diagnostics
 .
 It is also used to help ensure proper upgrades, so it is recommended that
 it not be removed.

Package: jolicloud-standard
Architecture: any
Depends: ${jolicloud-standard:Depends}
Recommends: ${jolicloud-standard:Recommends}
Breaks: ${jolicloud-standard:Breaks}
Conflicts: ubuntu-standard
Provides: ubuntu-standard
Replaces: ubuntu-standard
Description: The Jolicloud standard system
 This package depends on all of the packages in the Jolicloud standard system.
 This set of packages provides a comfortable command-line Unix-like
 environment.
 .
 It is also used to help ensure proper upgrades, so it is recommended that
 it not be removed.

